# which deliberately uses typographic punctuation (em-dashes, ellipses) in
# comments and docs. Keeping these files byte-identical to upstream keeps
# `git merge upstream/main` clean. New code outside these prefixes (notably
# src/, which is ASCII-clean) must pass the check.
